              "subject": "[PATCH v2] btrfs: write-protect folios during data writeback",
              "date": "2026-07-15T00:21:03Z"
            }
          ],
          "series_items": [],
          "patch_summary": "This patch adds write-protection for folios during data writeback in the Btrfs file system to prevent corruption and data loss due to concurrent writes by processes with an mmap-ed file. The patch addresses issues related to large folios, subpage sectorsize, zoned submissions, inline extents, and EOF-spanning folios, where a process can modify a sector while it is being used by writeback without faulting, leading to corruption or lost writes.",
          "analysis_source": "llm-per-reviewer",
          "review_comments": [
            {
              "author": "Qu Wenruo",
              "summary": "Reviewer noted that the patch does not handle the case where a task with an existing mmap-ed PTE writes to a folio before it is fully submitted and the dirty bit is cleared, which can result in losing the write even if fsync() is called.",
              "sentiment": "NEEDS_WORK",
              "sentiment_signals": [
                "Requested changes"
              ],
